President Obama has nominated Judge David Campos Guaderrama to serve on the United States District Court bench for the Western District of Texas. Judge Guaderrama has been a United States Magistrate Judge in the Western District of Texas since October 2010 and has previously served as a District Judge for the 243rd District Court of Texas in El Paso. He also worked as El Paso County's first Chief Public Defender. Judge Guaderrama received his J.D. from the University of Notre Dame Law School and his B.A. from New Mexico State University. President Obama praised Judge Guaderrama's integrity and commitment to justice, stating that he will be a valuable addition to the federal bench for the people of Texas.